============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is metabolism?
A1: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q2: What is the internet?
A2: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q3: What is osmosis?
A3: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q4: What is the greenhouse effect?
A4: Greenhouse gases (CO2, methane) trap heat radiated from
     Earth's surface. Natural effect warms Earth; human
     emissions intensify it causing climate change.

Q5: What is a programming language?
A5: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

